HEADWORD: Originality
<hw>O*rig`i*nal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>originalit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or
state of being original.</def> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Ability to create new and original ideas, works of
art, theories, etc.; ability to express oneself in an original manner;
creativity; -- of people.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Originally</ent>⟦br⟧
